<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900418-0157</DOCNO><DOCID>900418-0157.</DOCID><HL>   Sweden's Tax Overhaul Plan</HL><DATE>04/18/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   EUROP TAXES</CO><LP>   STOCKHOLM -- The Swedish government said domestichouseholds' disposable income would increase 2% next year,under the final version of the tax overhaul proposal itunveiled Tuesday.   The Social Democratic minority government also proposed inthe document to allow companies to deduct 65% of the value oftheir stock in foreign units. The revisions, which aim to cutand simplify taxes while broadening the tax base over atwo-year period, reduce the top marginal tax to 50% from80.2%.</LP><TEXT>   State tax will be canceled on wages of up to 180,000kronor ($29,502), and those wage earners will pay only cityor local council tax of about 30%. About 85% of all taxpayerswill pay only the local tax.   The 76 billion-krona ($12.46 billion) overhaul isguaranteed passage by the Riksdag, Sweden's parliament,despite the goverment's lack of majority after its deal withthe opposition Liberal Party last week.</TEXT></DOC>